Kaveel Singh, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Four children at a facility for troubled boys have allegedly killed a supervisor there, KwaZulu-Natal police said on Tuesday. The 40-year-old man was a supervisor at the Excelsior Place of Safety in Pinetown, Captain Nqobile Gwala said.&ldquo;He was found with multiple stab wounds on Monday. The motive of the killing is unknown at this stage.&rdquo;Pinetown police are investigating a case of murder and following up on the suspects.Excelsior Place of Safety is a government organisation that accommodates boys aged 13 to 17. It runs a short-term residential facility together with an intervention programme that is intended to help boys awaiting trial.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.